title: Texas A&M LB Otaro Alaka out for Season
text:
Home » Sports » Texas A&M LB Otaro Alaka out for Season Texas A&M LB Otaro Alaka out for Season Posted by Zach Taylor Sports Tuesday, October 20th, 2015 
Texas A&M head coach Kevin Sumlin has announced that sophomore linebacker Otaro Alaka will miss the rest of the season after undergoing surgery for a torn labrum. 
Alaka, a Cy-Falls product, appeared in three games for the Aggies this season, starting two of them and collecting 12 total tackles. 
As a freshman in 2014, Alaka played in all 12 games and made 33 tackles. He was also named the Liberty Bowl Defensive MVP in Texas A&M’s 45-37 victory over West Virginia.
